senate republican leader bob dole discarding 
normal senate courtesies ignored another gop senators 
longstanding objections thursday night and permitted confirmation 
of a backlog of 45 presidential nominees 
the action filled diplomatic vacancies many of them months old 
at us embassies in nations around the world including el 
salvador lebanon syria bolivia and colombia 
dole said the senate logjam had been caused by sen gordon 
humphrey rnh who had used senate tradition to place a hold 
on president reagans nomination of veteran foreign service officer 
christopher w s ross to be the new us ambassador to algeria 
humphrey apparently had no objections to ross personally but was 
using his senate privileges to gain leverage on an unrelated issue 
he sought to pressure the state department to name a special 
us envoy to resistance forces in afghanistan to coordinate us 
policy during the withdrawal of soviet occupying forces from that 
country 
dole said he had just received a handwritten note from deputy 
secretary of state john whitehead reading in part to solve sen 
humphreys problem we will appoint a special envoy for 
afghanistan 
but the republican leader said he could not find humphrey who 
was away from the senate floor 
nor could he locate any member of humphreys staff 
the senate was about to adjourn until sept 7 on its annual 
labor day recess 
dole said he was reluctant to have the nominations delayed so 
long 
there are 45 nominations being tied up here dole said 
he said he then called whitehead who confirmed the state 
department will appoint a special envoy for afghanistan 
he said he cannot go as far as senator humphrey wants on the 
powers such an envoy will have but he is going to make the 
appointment dole reported 
dole said he was handling the ross nomination separately from 
the others to create a separate record so senator humphrey 
understands we did not do this lightly 
under the circumstances dole said i feel justified in 
waiving senator humphreys hold on the nominee 
the senate then moved by voice votes to confirm the other 
delayed nominees 
at a news conference earlier this week humphrey urged certain 
gop presidential nominee george bush to select a conservative 
running mate 
he replied affirmatively when asked if he would strike dole from 
the list 
dole made no mention of humphreys statement as he acted to end 
the delay on the nominations caused by the new hampshire senators 
objections 
those confirmed included ross and edward p djerejian to be 
ambassador to syria john t mccarthy to be ambassador to lebanon 
thomas e mcnamara to be ambassador to colombia robert s gelbard 
to be ambassador to bolivia john f kordek to be ambassador to 
botswana carl c cundiff to be ambassador to niger john a 
burroughs jr to be ambassador to uganda robert l pugh to be 
ambassador to chad and william h twaddell to be ambassador to 
mauritania 
other confirmed nominations included those of william h fite to 
be an assistant director of the arms control and disarmament 
agency martin h newlin to represent the united states at the 
international atomic energy agency and don e newquist to be a 
member of the us international trade commission 
