<TEXT>
the united nations is operating seven 
peacekeeping and observer forces including the justformed 
observer group to monitor the iraniraq ceasefire 
the forces are funded in a variety of ways some are included in 
the regular un budget some are paid by special peacekeeping 
assessments and some receive voluntary contributions the general 
assembly must authorize funding for major expenditures 
here is a look at the existing forces and their financing 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
name un iraniraq military observer group 
created aug 9 1988 
location iraniraq border war front region 
headquarters not yet established iran and iraq are to provide 
necessary offices and facilities 
mission to observe ceasefire to take effect aug 20 monitor 
iraqi and iranian troops withdrawals to their own countries and 
assist the implementation of un security council resolution 598 
which also calls for an exchange of prisoners of war 
participating countries argentina australia austria 
bangladesh canada denmark finland ghana hungary indonesia 
india ireland italy kenya malaysia new zealand nigeria 
norway poland senegal sweden turkey yugoslavia and zambia 
strength 350 observers 
financing the group is expected to cost 74 million over a 
sixmonth period the means of funding is still being worked out 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
name un good offices mission in afghanistan and pakistan 
created april 14 1988 
location afghanistan 
headquarters kabul afghanistan and islamabad pakistan 
mission to monitor soviet troop withdrawal from afghanistan 
which is to be complete by feb 15 1989 
participating countries the observers were dispatched from 
other existing un peacekeeping and military observation groups 
approximate strength 50 
financing the afghanistan observer force does not have a 
separate budget and may dissolve in february when all soviet 
troops are to be out of afghanistan 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
name un disengagement observer force 
created june 3 1974 
location syrian golan heights 
headquarters damascus syria 
mission to supervise ceasefire between israel and syria after 
the 1974 middle east war 
participating countries austria canada finland poland 
approximate strength 1330 
financing the united nations has assessed its 159 members 
about 35 million for the 1988 expenses of the un disengagement 
observer force and its subsidiary arabisraeli peacekeeping 
operations payable to the uns special peacekeeping budget 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
name un interim force in lebanon 
created march 19 1978 
location southern lebanon 
headquarters naqoura lebanon 
