caused mostly by price increases rather than an increase in sales 
volume and 02 percent at restaurants and bars 
drug stores reported a 10 percent drop in july sales while 
gasoline stations reported a 02 percent decline 
overall sales for the first seven months of the year were 65 
percent greater than the same period in 1987 about two percentage 
points above the rate of inflation 
