fortythree years after her husband died in 
office and 26 years after her own death eleanor roosevelt is the 
presidents wife most admired by american women according to a 
poll in the september ladies home journal 
the wife of franklin d roosevelt was named by 28 percent of the 
women surveyed for the magazine by the roper organization 
nancy reagan the incumbent first lady was second with 26 
percent 
the rest of the mostadmired were jacqueline onassis widow of 
john f kennedy 20 percent betty ford 17 percent rosalynn 
carter 11 percent patricia nixon 7 percent lady bird johnson 
and mamie eisenhower 6 percent each and bess truman 5 percent 
the percentages add up to more than 100 because some of those 
polled named more than one 
the poll conducted among 1000 women during the third week of 
april is projectable for the entire country with an error margin 
of 3 percent the magazine said 
sixtynine percent of the women polled said that when a 
president and his wife disagree on a controversial issue she 
should keep quiet about it in public twentyfive percent said she 
