the disasterrelief measure among other things provides aid 
for farmers suffering crop losses of more than 35 percent of their 
expected harvest because of the drought or other calamities the 
payments would be equal to 65 percent of the lost income farmers 
whose crop losses exceeded 75 percent of the expected yield would 
receive payments equal to 90 percent of lost income 
the measure also makes feed assistance available for producers 
of many varieties of livestock including cattle sheep goats 
pigs poultry horses used for food or in food production and fish 
used for food 
money for the payments is expected to come from savings that the 
government will realize as a result of the drought since farm 
