<TEXT>
the federal communications commission is 
satisfied with us sprint communications cos efforts to resolve 
billing complaints from its longdistance telephone customers an 
fcc official said thursday 
from our perspective the matter is closed said greg vogt 
chief of the enforcement division of the fccs common carrier 
bureau 
the fcc had sent us sprint a letter last month warning the phone 
company that it faced sanctions unless it did a better job 
responding to billing complaints 
the agency ordered us sprint to explain the procedures it has in 
place to investigate complaints forwarded by the fcc and outline 
what steps the company intended to take to speed resolution of 
these complaints 
in response to the letter us sprint earlier this week told the 
fcc it is getting fewer complaints about billing problems and that 
the problems are being resolved more quickly 
the fccs concern focused on the complaints that the agency 
receives from us sprint customers and forwards to the company at 
the time the letter was sent vogt said these complaints likely 
were far fewer than the number of customer complaints sent directly 
to us sprint 
but us sprint says it is well on the way to resolving the 
billing problems that plagued the company after it was formed in 
july 1986 as a joint venture of gte corps sprint and united 
telecommunications us telecom united telecommunications will take 
a majority ownership of us sprint later this year 
us sprint officials have blamed much of their billing problems 
on the merging of the two phone systems 
we think the severe billing problems we had in the past are 
pretty much behind us said leon kestenbaum a us sprint vice 
president who met with fcc officials about the matter on wednesday 
there are always going to be some things that arent perfect 
but basically we think the problem is well over 90 percent 
solved he said 
vogt said the agency was very pleased with us sprints 
efforts to resolve quickly customer complaints about bills he 
added that the fcc will continue to monitor the companys 
performance and well see in the next few months whether they 
live up to their promises 
us sprint is the nations thirdlargest longdistance company 
after american telephone amp telegraph co and mci communications 
corp 
</TEXT>
