<TEXT>
scandinavian airline system has 
agreed to buy 40 percent of the national carrier aerolineas 
argentinas for 204 million the government announced thursday 
the agreement was signed by the director of public enterprises 
horacio losoviz and sas vice president for strategic planning 
terje sunde johnsen according to the government news agency telam 
the agreement now goes to president raul alfonsin and then 
congress for ratification 
the sale is part of alfonsins privatization plans whereby 
state enterprises particularly unprofitable ones are being sold 
to private investors the intention is to reduce the drain on the 
cashstrapped public treasury and improve services 
the government will retain 51 percent of aerolineas argentinas 
the remaining 9 percent will be sold to employees 
